Boasson Hagen Wins 17th Stage of Tour de France; Voeckler Stays in Lead

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-07-20T15:02:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/boasson-hagen-wins-17th-stage-of-tour-de-france-voeckler-stays-in-lead.html
Edvald Boasson Hagen of  Norway  won
the 17th stage of cycling’s Tour de  France , a 111-mile Alpine
trip from Gap to Pinerolo in  Italy . It was the Team Sky rider’s
second win on this year’s Tour.  Thomas Voeckler  of France keeps the race leader’s
yellow jersey.  The 21-stage race ends in Paris on July 24.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at  at
 celser@bloomberg.net  